      "officialText": "2025-26 2\nRiverdale Unified School District\nPublic Information\nNon-Discrimination District Statement\nThe Governing Board is committed to providing equal opportunity for all individuals in\neducation. District programs, activities, and practices shall be free from unlawful\ndiscrimination, including discrimination against an individual or group based on race,\ncolor, ancestry, nationality, national origin, ethnic group identification, age, religion,\nmarital, pregnancy, or parental status, physical or mental disability, sex, sexual\norientation, gender, immigration status, gender identity or expression, or genetic\ninformation; a perception of one or more of such characteristics; or association with a\nperson or group with one or more of these actual or perceived characteristics. (Ed.\nCode §§ 234.7)\nSpecial Education Records\nRiverdale Joint Unified School District maintains Special Education records for students\nuntil they reach age 25. Special Education records of students with a year of birth on or\nbefore 2000 including Individualized Education Plans (IEPs), will be destroyed at the\nend of the 2025 calendar year. If you wish to obtain a copy of your records, you may\ncontact Carina Rodriguez at 559-867-8200 prior to December 31, 2025.",
