      "officialText": "2025-26 8\nTARDY/CUTS PROCEDURES\nIf a student is not in class when the bell rings, the student is tardy.\nThere is a 4-minute pass time between classes. At four (4) minutes, a tardy bell will sound to\ndesignate the start of class.\nFive (5) or more minutes late to class after the bell rings is considered a cut. A class cut will\nresult in a loss of 5 citizenship points and the assignment of a lunch detention.\nUpon receiving a total of 4 tardies in any combination of classes, a student will receive a\nwarning notice through a discipline mailing. Upon receiving 8 tardies, 5 citizenship points will be\ndeducted and a lunch detention will be assigned. With each additional series of 4 tardies (12,\n16, 20, etc.), a student will be deducted 5 citizenship points and will be assigned 1 day of After\nSchool Detention (3:20-6:15). Habitual tardiness may be cause for a parent meeting, the\nplacement of a student on a reassessment contract, or consideration for placement at an\nalternative school site.\nTARDY SWEEPS\n1. Tardy Sweeps will be conducted at random by school administration.\n2. Students caught in a Tardy Sweep will be sent to class once they have obtained a pass\nfrom an administrator and will be assigned a mandatory lunch detention on that day or\nthe following day.\nADMITTANCE OF STUDENTS TO CLASS\n1. Students who reach school after 8:10 a.m. must report to the main office for a late slip.\n2. Students who are late to class because they were held over by another teacher or\nsummoned to the office must have a hall pass.\nSTUDENTS WHO DO NOT HAVE THE APPROPRIATE PASS/SLIP WILL NOT BE\nADMITTED TO CLASS",
