      "officialText": "2025-26 9\nRIVERDALE HIGH SCHOOL\n ATTENDANCE REQUIREMENTS\n10 Absences\n(Per Semester for Each\nCourse for Course\nCredit)\n• Saturday school will be mandated for each absence exceeding 10 in a course per\nsemester. Attending one Saturday school will replace one absence in each class.\nStudents who complete the semester with more than 10 absences in a class will lose\ncredits for that class. (BP 5121 – Students exceeding 10 absences in a course are\nsubject to losing credit for that course even if a passing grade is earned).\nAbsences are\nNotes From\nParents/Guardians\n• cutting class, suspensions, staying home because you do not feel well, doctors and\ndentists appointments, or just not coming to school. If the student misses school\nfor ANY reason, that absence (excused or not) will be counted against the student.\nThis DOES INCLUDE staying home with a headache, etc. even though your parent sends a\nnote or calls the school stating you were ill. It DOES NOT INCLUDE school sponsored\ntrips.\n• regarding students who are ill: students need a note stating the reason they are\nabsent, and it must be signed by their parent/guardian.\nSpecial\nCircumstances\nFor Petition\nInclude\n• a hospital stay, etc. or other special circumstances must be submitted to the\nprincipal for review. The parent or guardian must submit the proper paperwork to\nthe principal in order to r eceive approval. Petitions will be accepted only for\ndeath in the immediate family, observance of a religious holiday, hospitalization\nand quarantine. A note from the doctor will be required for quarantine. Please see\nthe school secretary/attendance cler k for the required paperwork to clear an\nabsence.\n Within two weeks of an absence, due to special circumstances, a petition accompanied\nwith proper documentation must be submitted to the Principal for review. Absences\nthat are reviewed and approved throug h the petition process will not be counted\ntowards the accumulated 10 absence policy to maintain credit with in a course.\nPlease see the school secretary/attendance clerk for the required paperwork to clear\nthe absence.\nTruancy\n(Year Long for Each\nCourse)\n• E.C. 48260(a) Any pupil subject to compulsory full-time education or to compulsory\ncontinuation education who is absent from school without valid excuse three full\ndays in one school year or tardy or absent for more than any 30-minute period during\nthe school day without a valid excuse on three occasions in one school year, or any\ncombination thereof, is a truant and shall be reported to the attendance supervisor\nor to the superintendent of the school district. Students will also be referred to\nSaturday School.\nStudents\n• will need to keep an accurate record of their attendance but may request a copy of\ntheir attendance record from the school secretary/attendance clerk\nAt the beginning of each school year, the Superintendent or designee shall send a notification to the\nparents/guardians of all students, and to all students in grades 7-12 informing them that school\nauthorities may excuse any student from school to obtain confidential medical services without the\nconsent of the student’s parent/guardian (Education Code 46010.1)Please see page 33 for a copy\nof the Riverdale Joint Unified School District’s Truancy or Excessive Absences Guidelines” and\nSchool Attendance Review Board (SARB) Process. (Education Code 48260(a)).",
