      "plain": "TL;DR: This section covers two high-interest areas: privileges and dress code. Students start each quarter with 40 citizenship points; falling below 25 puts a student on the Nonprivileged List. Dress code rules also limit pajamas, undergarments as outerwear, straps, midriffs, hair color, tattoos, hats/hoods indoors, red/blue clothing, bulldogs, and certain sports apparel.",
      "student": "Check both your points and your outfit. If you lose too many citizenship points, you can lose access to dances, games, clubs, or activities. For clothing, assume “it depends” and check the details before wearing pajamas, red/blue, sports gear, unusual hair color, crop tops, or anything that exposes undergarments.",
