      "officialText": "2025-26 11\nDISCIPLINARY POLICIES AND CONSEQUENCES\nNONPRIVILEGED LIST\nStudents on the Nonprivilege d List may not attend any Riverdale Unified School District extracurricular\nactivity or co -curricular activities beyond the expectations and requirements of the curriculum (includes\nathletic events, club/class activities, dances, etc.) on or off school grounds.\nEvery student begins each quarter with forty (40) citizenship points. Points are deducted for noted discipline\noffenses.\nStudents who fall below twenty-five (25) citizenship points earn one week on the Nonprivilege d List in\naddition to other imposed consequences. Additional losses of points earn additional weeks on the\nNonprivileged List as listed below:\n Student Falls Below Consequence\n 25 points : 1 week on Nonprivileged List\n 15 points : 1 additional week on Nonprivileged List\n 10 points : 1 additional week on Nonprivilege d List (and\nparent conference with assistant principal)\n 5 points : Student is on the Nonprivilege d List until the\nbeginning of the next quarter, which may be\ncarried over into the next semester.\n 0 points : Student will be considered for a reassessment\ncontract or an alternative educational program\n*Students will not have the opportunity to earn back citizenship points during a quarter. Points are\nre-established at the end of each quarter throughout the school year.\n RJUSD Dress Code\nThe purpose of these standards of dress and grooming is to promote the education of students,\nteaching, and a secure and safe learning environment consistent with Board policy.\nAll clothing shall be neat, clean, and acceptable in repair and appearance, and shall be worn\nwithin the bounds of decency and good taste as appropriate for school.\n1. Pajamas (including pajama pants and onesies) shall not be worn to school.\n2. Clothing shall be sufficient to conceal undergarments at all times. This may require use of a belt\nto support pants at the waist. Undergarments may not be worn as outerwear. This includes but is\nnot limited to onesies, bodysuits, lingerie, or shapewear.\n3. Articles of clothing or apparel which could be considered gang related, contain profanity or\nproducts or slogans which promote tobacco, alcohol, drugs or sex, or those which create disorder\nor disrupt the educational process are not allowed. Long coats (e.g. trench coats) are not\npermitted.\n4. Tank tops halter tops, bare midriffs or bare chests, see-through outfits, or off the shoulder\nblouses are not appropriate or acceptable. Straps must be at least 1 inch in width. Spaghetti\nstraps are not permitted.\n5. Skirts and shorts shall be of appropriate length and shall not distract from the educational\nprocess. At minimum, length of skirts and shorts shall be reasonably close to mid-thigh.\n6. All students must wear shoes. Appropriate footwear must be worn for physical education.\nClosed toe shoes must be worn in shop classes.\n7. Official school headwear, along with solid white, gray, black, or green hats/caps may be worn on\ncampus. Hats, hoods, and sunglasses must be removed when indoors.\n\n2025-26 12\n8. Hair and facial hair shall be neatly groomed. Hair that causes undue attention is not permitted.\nThis includes unusual or extreme designs, colors, symbols, razor cuts, or messages. Hair shall\nbe a naturally occurring color (e.g. black, brown, blond, or natural red.\n9. Tattoos, permanent or temporary, must be covered at all times.\nCertain rules in the dress code will be relaxed on designated activity, dress-up, or spirit days. For\nexample, pajamas will be allowed on “Pajama Day.”\nPROHIBITED SPORTS APPAREL\nDue to gang affiliation, the following college/professional team sports apparel will not be allowed:\nChicago Bulls Dallas Cowboys Georgia Bulldogs Oakland Raiders\nChicago Cubs Duke University Kansas City Royals Philadelphia Phillies\nChicago White Sox Florida State L.A. Dodgers San Francisco 49ers\nCleveland Browns Fresno State Bulldogs* Michigan U.N.L.V.\nColorado Rockies Georgetown New York Yankees U.S.C.\n*In the spir it of a college going culture, RHS students will be allowed to wear Fresno State apparel, so\nlong as it does not contain the Bulldogs Logo.\nAlso, any apparel with a bulldog will not be allowed, whether or not it is associated with a sports team.\n No solid red or blue apparel will be allowed, with the exception of collared shirts.\nStudents who wear excessive red or blue may be given a dress code violation. This is at the\ndetermination of school administration.\nThe Board grants the administration the authority to modify and/or adopt more restrictive apparel\nand grooming policies due to repeated and/or excessive violations by a single student, group of\nstudents, or the student body.\nDISCIPLINE POLICY\nThe intent of school and classroom rules is to provide the best possible school environment for maximum\nlearning. These are basic discipline rules which will help give each student the right to learn and each\nteacher the right to teach.\nCLASSROOM RULES:\n 1. Be on time and prepared.\n 2. Do not disrupt learning or teaching.\n 3. No food or drinks in classrooms or hallways. Gum or seeds are not allowed on campus.\n 4. Be courteous, respectful and cooperative.\nGENERAL RULES:\n 1. Remain on campus.\n 2. Obey supervisor on duty.\n 3. Follow school and campus rules.\n 4. Behavior in restrooms, halls, etc. is to be appropriate.\n 5. Report to classroom when bell rings.\n Positive behavior will be emphasized and rewarded using the RHS Cowboy C.O.D.E. Incentive Program.\nFailure to display behavior expectation s or violation of school rules will result in disciplinary\nconsequences which can include, but are not limited to one or more of the following: loss of citizenship\npoints, detention (lunch or after school) community service, PBIS behavior response, loss of privileges\nand/or eligibility, suspension and expulsion.",
