      "officialText": "2025-26 23\nCLOSED CAMPUS\nRiverdale High School maintains a closed campus. Students may not leave campus during the school day,\nincluding during the lunch period. After school, campus will be closed to students not in the direct\nsupervision of an adult who is assigned to an athletic team or after school program component. Students are\nnot to leave campus and return to campus during the afterschool program.\nHALL PASSES\nThere will be one standard hall pass which will be used by teachers to send students to the office or\nrestroom. This same hall pass will be used by the office to send for students. Students are not to be out of\nclass without a hall pass.\nPERSONAL TELEPHONE CALLS\nStudents are not to use the phone in the main office at anytime, unless permission is given by the office\npersonnel.\nOFF-CAMPUS PERMITS\nOff-campus permits are issued in the main office. Permits will be issued only by consent of parents or\nguardians of the student. Permits issued will be verified by the main office prior to departure. No\nstudent should leave campus for any reason without clearing their departure through the main office.\nProcedure:\n1. Off-campus permits will be issued for the following reasons:\n a. Illness, verified by school personnel. At no time is a student to leave school and go home ill without\nfirst being cleared through the main office.\n\n2025-26 24\n b. Appointment with a doctor or dentist. The stamp of the doctor or dentist must be obtained and\npresented at the main office when returning to school.\n c. Illness and/or death in the family or funeral attendance when verified by parent or guardian.\n d. Off-campus permits may be issued for reasons other than medical purposes if special permission is\ngranted from the main office and only with the consent of parent or guardian.\n STUDENTS WILL NOT BE RELEASED TO ANY PARTY NOT LISTED ON THE CONTACT LIST.",
