      "officialText": "2025-26 31\nTruancy or Excessive Absences\nGuidelines\nFirst Notification of Truancy or Excessive Absences\nOn the 4th day of unjustified absences, the “First Notification of Truancy or Excessive\nAbsences” (letter 1) is to be mailed.\nSecond Notification of Truancy or excessive Absences\nOn the 5th day of unjustified absences, the “Second Notification of Truancy or Excessive\nAbsences” (letter 2) is to be mailed. An appointment is to be made to meet with the\nSchool Attendance review Team (SART), which will consist of the Principal, Assistant\nPrincipal and local law enforcement (Deputy), when possible, is to be scheduled.\nThird Notification of Continued Truancy\nOn the 6th day of unjustified absences, the “Third Notification of Continued Truancy’\n(letter 3) is to be mailed. A second meeting with the School Principal and local law\nenforcement (Deputy), when possible, is to be scheduled.\nNotification Letter of SARB Referral\nOn the 7th day of unjustified absences, the “Notification Letter of SARB Referral” (letter\n4) is to be mailed. The Principal is to notify the family that this matter has been referred\nto the School Attendance Review Board and that a hearing will be held.\nFourth Notification of Truancy\nThe “Fourth Notification of Truancy (letter 5) will be sent by the District notifying the\nfamily that they are required to attend a scheduled SARB hearing. If the\nparents/guardians do not assume responsibility for their child’s truancy at this point, the\nDistrict will proceed with other legal referrals.",
