      "officialText": "RIVERDALE UNIFIED SCHOOL DISTRICT\nFOGGY DAY SCHEDULE\n2025-2026\n We will be following the procedures outlined below for the 2025-2026 school year.\n Please keep this notice for reference.\n*** Parents and students may be informed of foggy day schedules by going directly to the Southwest\nTransportation Agency website, www.southwestjpa.org. Notification of a foggy day schedule is also\nposted on Channel 18. It will broadcast schools with foggy day schedules from 5:45 a.m. to 12 noon.\nRadio stations 580 and 107.5 will also broadcast foggy day schedules. It will be announced we are on\nPlan A, Plan B, or Plan C. Fipps Primary, Riverdale Elementary, Riverdale High and Horizon High\nSchools operate their buses as 1 unit. If a “Foggy Day Schedule” is called for one school, it will apply to\nall schools in the District.\n PLAN A\n 1. Classes start at 10:00 a.m.\n 2. Buses run about 1 hour 45 minutes later than the regular day schedule.\n 3. Students are to be at school between 9:30 a.m. and 10:00 a.m.\n * Absences or tardiness due to unsafe weather or fog conditions (when a parent/guardian\n is unable to transport their student safely) are excused upon parent/guardian notification\n to the school.\n 4. Classes are dismissed for the day at Fipps Primary School at 3:15 p.m., 3:30 p.m. at\n Riverdale Elementary School, and 3:45 p.m. at Riverdale High School.\n 5. Foggy Days will be called on a daily basis, unless you are informed otherwise.\n PLAN B\n 1. Buses run about 2 hours and 45 minutes later than the regular day schedule.\n a. Occasionally, fog conditions persist and a decision is made to delay bus service for\n 2 hours and 45 minutes.\n b. Channel 18 is notified and broadcasts the update, “Plan B”. Classes start at 10:00 a.m.\n *NOTE: Berylwood stops will be at 9:45 a.m. on Plan A or B\n PLAN C\n 1. Morning buses are canceled. Afternoon buses will transport students. Classes start at\n 10:00 a.m.\nPROCEDURES FOR CALLING A FOGGY DAY SCHEDULE\n The following procedures have been reviewed for determining if a foggy day schedule should be\ncalled:\n 1. Individuals living in the District are contacted to determine if a foggy situation exists in\n their respective areas.\n 2. If one of the contacts reports fog conditions relative to guidelines, a foggy day schedule\n will be implemented for the day.\nNOTE: *Each contact is asked to determine the fog conditions by clearly sighting an object\n (a light) 200 feet away.\n*If a Foggy Day is called on an Early Release Monday, we will follow a regular Foggy Day\nSchedule.",
