      "pdfPage": 15,
      "handbookPage": "10",
      "text": "2025-26 10\n EXPANDED LEARNING PROGRAM\nMission of Expanded Learning Program\nThe Expanded Learning Program promotes a safe and positive environment for Riverdale High School\nstudents to continue to achieve both academic and personal success through educational and\nenrichment opportunities. After Hours is open to all Riverdale High School students for the following:\n1. Additional Support Opportunities scheduled with staff\n2. Athletics\n3. Cyber High Credit Recovery Program\nDuring the school year, the Expanded Learning program is open.\nSchedule\nProgram runs from the time school is out until 6:00 p.m. Students must sign up daily for the late bus.\nLate Bus departs at 6:15 p.m. from the bus parking lot.\nExpanded Learning Program Rules\nStudents are to be responsible and must:\n(1) Students must sign in to their assigned after ELP area no later than 3:25 on regular school days and\nby 2:10 on Early Release Mondays. Students MAY NOT LEAVE CAMPUS between the end of classes\nand the start time of the ELP. Once signed in, students may not leave unless given permission by ASP\nsupervisor.\nStudents who fail to follow the above rules will be held accountable for the following consequences:\nStudent Step Consequence\n1 : Verbal warning by RHS administration, incident documented, parent contact\n2 : Verbal warning by RHS administration, incident documented, parent contact\n3 : Student is dropped from Expanded Learning Program and loses eligibility for the\nremainder of the season. Incident documented, parent contact."
