      "text": "2025-26 12\n8. Hair and facial hair shall be neatly groomed. Hair that causes undue attention is not permitted.\nThis includes unusual or extreme designs, colors, symbols, razor cuts, or messages. Hair shall\nbe a naturally occurring color (e.g. black, brown, blond, or natural red.\n9. Tattoos, permanent or temporary, must be covered at all times.\nCertain rules in the dress code will be relaxed on designated activity, dress-up, or spirit days. For\nexample, pajamas will be allowed on “Pajama Day.”\nPROHIBITED SPORTS APPAREL\nDue to gang affiliation, the following college/professional team sports apparel will not be allowed:\nChicago Bulls Dallas Cowboys Georgia Bulldogs Oakland Raiders\nChicago Cubs Duke University Kansas City Royals Philadelphia Phillies\nChicago White Sox Florida State L.A. Dodgers San Francisco 49ers\nCleveland Browns Fresno State Bulldogs* Michigan U.N.L.V.\nColorado Rockies Georgetown New York Yankees U.S.C.\n*In the spir it of a college going culture, RHS students will be allowed to wear Fresno State apparel, so\nlong as it does not contain the Bulldogs Logo.\nAlso, any apparel with a bulldog will not be allowed, whether or not it is associated with a sports team.\n No solid red or blue apparel will be allowed, with the exception of collared shirts.\nStudents who wear excessive red or blue may be given a dress code violation. This is at the\ndetermination of school administration.\nThe Board grants the administration the authority to modify and/or adopt more restrictive apparel\nand grooming policies due to repeated and/or excessive violations by a single student, group of\nstudents, or the student body.\nDISCIPLINE POLICY\nThe intent of school and classroom rules is to provide the best possible school environment for maximum\nlearning. These are basic discipline rules which will help give each student the right to learn and each\nteacher the right to teach.\nCLASSROOM RULES:\n 1. Be on time and prepared.\n 2. Do not disrupt learning or teaching.\n 3. No food or drinks in classrooms or hallways. Gum or seeds are not allowed on campus.\n 4. Be courteous, respectful and cooperative.\nGENERAL RULES:\n 1. Remain on campus.\n 2. Obey supervisor on duty.\n 3. Follow school and campus rules.\n 4. Behavior in restrooms, halls, etc. is to be appropriate.\n 5. Report to classroom when bell rings.\n Positive behavior will be emphasized and rewarded using the RHS Cowboy C.O.D.E. Incentive Program.\nFailure to display behavior expectation s or violation of school rules will result in disciplinary\nconsequences which can include, but are not limited to one or more of the following: loss of citizenship\npoints, detention (lunch or after school) community service, PBIS behavior response, loss of privileges\nand/or eligibility, suspension and expulsion."
