      "pdfPage": 19,
      "handbookPage": "14",
      "text": "2025-26 14\nDISCIPLINARY PROCEDURES FOR SPECIFIC OFFENSES\nThe Mission Statement of Riverdale Unified School District focuses on student learning and achievement.\nAll staff members are assigned the duty of assisting and supporting students. The success of our students\ncan only be accomplished in an environment that is safe and orderly and one that will not t olerate any\ndisruption of the educational process.\nThe District rules/regulations and procedures governing suspension and expulsion are on file at the District\nOffice for your inspection.\nThe District employs a detection canine program that identifies the possible presence of drugs or weapons.\nThe canine program is applied to classrooms, parking lots, other facilities and student belongings only.\nThe specific consequences listed in this section are minimum consequences only. Consequences may be\nextended at the discretion of the administrator after considering the severity of the offense.\nAll school suspensions may either be on-campus suspensions, or removal from school, as deemed\nappropriate.\nFactors such as the seriousness of the offense, the circumstances under which it occurred, and\nthe student's past record will be considered in deciding what disciplinary action will be taken. The\nadministration of Riverdale High School reserves the right to decide what course of action will be\napplied.\nThe following rules have been designed to provide students with a safe and orderly environment.\n1. WEAPONS, FIRECRACKERS, AND/OR EXPLOSIVES\n The possession of a firearm, knife, explosive or other dangerous object of no reasonable use to\nthe pupil at school or at a school related function is prohibited. All cases will be reported to the\nproper law enforcement agencies.\n Any Offense - Loss of ten (10) to thirty (30) citizenship points, suspension and recommendation\nto the Superintendent for expulsion.\n2. ARSON, A SSAULT & BATTERY, POSSESSION OF ALCOHOL, DRUGS, AND/OR DRUG\nPARAPHERNALIA, HARASSMENT OF ANY FORM , SEXUAL ASSAULT -BATTERY,\nROBBERY & EXTORTION OR THREATS ON SCHOOL PERSONNEL OR STUDENTS\n In all cases of arson, robbery, or extortion, restitution will be made by student or legal guardian for\nlosses or damages to school buildings, school property, or possessions of students, staff\nmembers, and visitors. All arson cases will be reported to the proper law enforcement agencies.\n Any of the above occurring at any time or place related to school functions will be reported to the\nproper law enforcement agencies.\n Any Offense - Loss of ten (10) to thirty (30) citizenship points, suspension and possible referral to\nan alternative educational program or recommendation to the Superintendent for expulsion.\n3. AMMUNITION\n The possession of ammunition at school or at a school related function is strictly prohibited.\nPossession of ammunition at school may be reported to law enforcement.\n Any Offense - Loss of ten (10) to thirty (30) citizenship points, and/or possible one (1) to five (5)\nday suspension. More serious or repeated violations could lead to placement in an alternative\neducation program or recommendation for expulsion."
