      "pdfPage": 21,
      "handbookPage": "16",
      "text": "2025-26 16\n First Offense - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points and one (1) day detention or one (1) day\nsuspension.\n Repeat Offenses - Loss of twenty (20) citizenship points and two (2) days detention or two (2)\ndays suspension.\n8. PORNOGRAPHY\nPossession or distribution of pornographic literature or materials, both published and electronic\non campus or at a school activity is prohibited.\nFirst Offense - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points and one (1) day detention or one (1 ) day\nsuspension.\nSecond Offense - Loss of twenty (20) citizenship points and three (3) days suspension and\npossible referral to an alternative educational program.\n9. ELECTRONIC DEVICES, INCLUDING CELL PHONES\n The use of cell phones or other electronic devices, including, but not limited to: iPods, PSP’s,\nPDAs and cameras are not allowed to be used on campus at any time that class is in session\n(8:10 – 3:15), unless permission has been given by school administration. The usage of\nelectronic devices is strictly prohibited when class is in session unless an instructor has given\npermission for the use of such a device for academic purposes. Students must turn such\ndevices off and keep them out of sight during class time.\n Cell phones and other electronic devices, may be used on campus before and after school and\nduring breaks and lunch. However, the use of such devices is subject to regulation by the\nschool. Students who violate this policy or other District rules while using such devices are\nsubject to disciplinary action. Students may use the office phone for urgent needs during class\ntime with permission from a staff member.\n A student is NOT allowed to take pictures of individuals without their consent. The taking of\npictures without consent is considered an invasion of privacy.\n First Offense – The item will be confiscated and turned in to the office. The student will receive\na loss of ten (10) citizenship points. Only a parent or guardian will be allowed to retrieve the\ndevice from administration.\n Second Offense – The item will be confiscated and turned in to the office. The student will\nreceive a one (1) day suspension and a loss of ten (10) citizenship points. Only a parent or\nguardian will be allowed to retrieve the device from administration.\n Third Offense – The item will be confiscated and turned in to the office. The student will receive\na three (3) day suspension and a loss of ten (10) citizenship points. Only a parent or guardian\nwill be allowed to retrieve the device from administration.\n No student shall be prohibited from possessing or using an electronic device that is determined\nby a licensed physician or surgeon to be essential for the student's health and the use of which\nis limited to health-related purposes. (Education Code 48902.5)\nThe District is not responsible for lost or stolen personal electronic devices and/or cellular/digital\ntelephones.\n10. INTERNET SAFETY POLICY\n Accessing inappropriate internet sites will result in the following consequences.\n First Offense – loss of ten (10) citizenship points and a loss of internet use for three (3) months.\n Second Offense – Loss of twenty (20) citizenship points a loss of internet use for one (1) year."
