      "pdfPage": 22,
      "handbookPage": "17",
      "text": "2025-26 17\n11. DEFIANCE, DISRESPECT, INSUBORDINATION\nStudents who willfully de fy the valid authority of school personnel and school rules or are\ndisrespectful, either in language or action, are subject to disciplinary action.\nFirst Offense - Loss of ten (10) to twenty (20) citizenship points and one (1) to three (3) day\ndetention, possible referral to counselor.\nSecond Offense - Loss of ten (10) to twenty (20) citizenship points and possible referral to\ncounselor.\nThird Offense - Loss of twenty (20 -30) citizenship points and consideration of referral to an\nalternative educational program.\n12. GAMBLING\nGambling on school grounds, including the pitching of coins, is prohibited.\nFirst Offense - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points and one (1) day detention or a one (1) day\nsuspension.\nSecond and Repeat Offenses - Loss of twenty (20) citiz enship points, three (3) to five (5) day\nsuspension and possible referral to an alternative educational program.\n 13. CUTTING CLASS, LOITERING, LEAVING CAMPUS WITHOUT PERMISSION\nStudents are not allowed to leave campus between the opening and closing of th e school day.\nExceptions will be made for those students with an off -campus permit approved by an\nadministrator.\nLess than five minutes to class is considered a tardy. Five minutes or more late to class is\nconsidered a cut.\nStudents may not leave campus. Students are not allowed to be on another school's campus\nwithout the permission of that school's administration.\nFirst Offense - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points for each offense or period cut (up to thirty (30)\npoints) and one (1) day detention or o ne (1) day Saturday School. A full day cut will result in a\nloss of thirty (30) points and a one (1) day Saturday School..\nSecond Offense - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points for each period cut (up to thirty (30) points)\nand three (3) days Saturday School, or three (3) days detention.\nThird Offense - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points for each period cut and suspension pending\nreferral to an alternative educational program for repeated defiance.\n14. CHEATING/PLAGIARISM\n First Offense - Loss of twenty (20) citizenship points and one (1) day detention or one (1) day\nsuspension. Student will receive an \"F\" grade for that assignment or test.\n Second Offense - Loss of thirty (30) citizenship points and two (2) days detention or two (2) days\nsuspension. Student will receive an \"F\" grade for that assignment or test. Teacher will contact\nparent.\n Third Offense - Loss of twenty (20) citizenship points and suspension of five (5) or more days\npending referral to an alternative educational program.\n15. AUDITORIUM/GYMNASIUM DISRUPTION AND/OR MISBEHAVIOR\n First Offense - Student will immediately be sent to the office and assigned one (1) day detention\nand the student will lose ten (10) citizenship points.\n Second Offense - Student will immediately be sent to the o ffice and assigned two (2) days\ndetention and the student will lose ten (10) citizenship points. The student will not be allowed to\nattend an assembly/performance for the remainder of the school year."
