      "pdfPage": 23,
      "handbookPage": "18",
      "text": "2025-26 18\n16. PROFANITY OR VULGARITY\n Use of profanity or vulgarity on campus or at a school event is prohibited.\n First Offense - Loss of five (5) citizenship points.\n Repeated offenses - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points and one (1) day detention or a one (1)\nday suspension.\n17. DRESS CODE VIOLATIONS\nAny student in violation of the dress code will be referred to an assistant principal. A student will\nnot return to class or participate in a school activity until he/she is in compliance with the dress\ncode.\nFirst Offense - Loss of five (5) citizenship points.\nSecond Offense - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points and one (1) day detention\nThird and Repeat Offense - Loss of twenty (20) citizenship points and one (1) day detention.\n18. PARKING LOT VIOLATIONS,\n Students may not go into the parking lot between th e opening and closing of the school day\nwithout prior administrative approval.\nFirst Offense - Loss of five (5) citizenship points.\nSecond Offense - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points and one (1) day detention.\nThird and Repeat Offense - Loss of twenty (20) citizenship points and one (1) day detention.\n19. PARKING PASS VIOLATION\nStudents parking within the student parking lot, the south side of the South Gym, must display a\nschool issued parking pass on their rear view mirror at all times. Those vehicles observed\nwithout a parking pass within the student parking lot are subject to the following discipline:\nFirst Offense: Warning and Parent Notification\nSecond and Repeat Offense: Loss of ten (10) to twenty (20) citizenship points and/or loss of\nparking privileges. More serious or repeated violations would lead to possible towing and\nimpoundment at owner’s expense.\n20. DISPLAYS OF AFFECTION\n Any inappropriate displays of affection will not be allowed on school campus or at school\nfunctions. Holding hands is acceptable.\n First Offense - Meeting with the assistant principal and the loss of five (5) citizenship points.\n Repeat Offenses - Loss of ten (10) citizenship points , referral for counseling and one (1) day\ndetention.\nMajor Offenses – Loss of ten (10) citizenship points, referral for counseling and one – five (1-5)\nday suspension\n21. BICYCLES AND SKATEBOARDS"
