      "text": "2025-26 28\n Softball Club: The mission is to make playing softball for Riverdale High School a positive, rewarding,\nand educational experience that will contribute to the players’ role as a student and to learn from their\nexperiences as a club member that will help them succeed after graduation.\n (Mr. Close – bclose@rjusd.org)\nDrama Club: The Drama Club offers students the opportunity to learn more about public speaking and\ntheater arts and to meet other students with similar interests. Students must be enrolled in a drama class\nto be eligible to participate in this organization or have a background and/or interest in theater arts or\nrecommended by the drama class teacher. (Ms. Jessup – cassidyjessup@rjusd.org)\nEclub: The eClub aims to provide a conduit by which students can access entrepreneurial resources,\nnetwork with community entrepreneurs, and share ideas. The club is dedicated to furthering\nunderstanding about new and small businesses. It is run in conjunction with the Small Business\nManagement course and the RHS School Store aka “The Supply Closet.” (Mr. Joe – ejoe@rjusd.org)\nFootball Club - The Football Club's mission is to make playing football for Riverdale High School a\npositive, rewarding, and educational experience that will contribute to the players' role as a student and to\nlearn from their experiences as a club member that will help them succeed after graduation. Bryan Close\n- bclose@rjusd.org\nFuture Farmers of America (FFA): The FFA is comprised of students who have an interest in agriculture.\n Students must be enrolled in an agriculture class to be eligible to participate in this national organization.\n Activities include showing livestock at local fairs, public speaking contests, judging contests and\nleadership conferences. (Ms. Garibaldi – morgangaribaldi@rjusd.org\nGay/Straight Alliance (GSA): The mission of the GSA is to promote understanding and acceptance of\nthe LGBT community, and all others, as it is understood that we live in a world with tremendous diversity\namongst its people. (Mrs. Nemeth – pnemeth@rjusd.org)\nSoccer Club: Their mission is to engage participants in the rewarding, motivated yet exciting sport while\nmaintaining the positive learning education experience. Every soccer player who participates will\ncontribute to the fun, motivation, and support of teammates providing essential elements of team work.\n(Mrs. Sunamoto – ashleysunamoto@rjusd.org)\nGolf Club: The Golf Club’s mission is to appreciate, respect, and enjoy the lifetime sport of golf. The club\nwill also promote proper course/life etiquette, management skills, friendships, and respect for other\nmembers of the club. (Mr. Banuelos – mbanuelos@rjusd.org)\nLeo Club: The RHS Leo Club provides the students of the Riverdale High School community with an\nopportunity for the development and contribution, individually and collectively, to serve as responsible\nmembers of their local, national, and international communities.\n(Mr. Reina– rreina@rjusd.org)\nPep & Cheer Club: The objective of the Pep Club is to promote school spirit, support the athletes through\nrallies and cheers and to aide the cheerleaders at rallies and games. Members must be students who\nare interested in school activities which promote school spirit in all areas of school life.\n(Ms.Garrett – mysteregarrett@rjusd.org)\nSoftball Club: The mission is to make playing softball for Riverdale High School a positive, rewarding, and\neducational experience that will contribute to the players’ role as a student and to learn from their\nexperiences as a club member that will help them succeed after graduation.\n (Mr. Close – bclose@rjusd.org)\nTennis Club: The Tennis Club’s mission is to appreciate and comprehend the sport of tennis as well as\npromote friendship and respect among its members. Anyone playing on the men’s or women’s tennis\nteam is eligible to join.\nTrack Club - The Track Club's mission is to make playing sports for Riverdale High School a positive,\nrewarding, and educational experience that will contribute to the players' role as a student and to learn\nfrom their experiences as a club member that will help them succeed after graduation"
